This paper deals with routing algorithms on graphs, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG) and data structures (cs.DS). The use of Delaunay triangulations is a common technique in computational geometry, further supporting cs.CG as the most likely category. The paper also discusses the use of headers in messages, which is relevant to network protocols (cs.NI) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper presents lower bounds on the competitive ratio, which is a topic in theoretical computer science (cs.SI).
